===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{liushu|p}} – rope wrapped around two pieces of wood to keep them straight.

Later borrowed phonetically to mean “[[no]]”. The derivative {{och-l|拂}} stands for the original word.

===Etymology 1===
; not (verb) him/her/it
: Fusion of {{och-l|不|not}} with {{och-l|之|''third-person pronoun''}} ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}). The glyph conflated with {{ltc-l|不}} by the Han times, due to naming taboo. Its colloquial reading survives in the latter. See etymology of {{zh-l|*不}} for more.

